{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.39",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 39,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 39",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 39 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:1",
      "text": "Say if thou knowest the time of the bringing forth of the wild goats of the rock, and if thou hast marked the calving of the hinds:",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:2",
      "text": "and if thou hast numbered the full months of their being with young, and if thou hast relieved their pangs:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:3",
      "text": "and hast reared their young without fear; and wilt thou loosen their pangs?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:4",
      "text": "Their young will break forth; they will be multiplied with offspring: their young will go forth, and will not return to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:5",
      "text": "And who is he that sent forth the wild ass free? and who loosed his bands?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:6",
      "text": "whereas I made his habitation the wilderness, and the salt land his coverts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:7",
      "text": "He laughs to scorn the multitude of the city, and hears not the chiding of the tax-gatherer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:8",
      "text": "He will survey the mountains as his pasture, and he seeks after every green thing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:9",
      "text": "And will the unicorn be willing to serve thee, or to lie down at thy manger?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:10",
      "text": "And wilt thou bind his yoke with thongs, or will he plough furrows for thee in the plain?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:11",
      "text": "And dost thou trust him, because his strength is great? and wilt thou commit thy works to him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:12",
      "text": "And wilt thou believe that he will return to thee thy seed, and bring it in to thy threshing-floor?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:13",
      "text": "The peacock has a beautiful wing: if the stork and the ostrich conceive, it is worthy of notice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:14",
      "text": "for the ostrich will leave her eggs in the ground, and warm them on the dust,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:15",
      "text": "and has forgotten that the foot will scatter them, and the wild beasts of the field trample them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:16",
      "text": "She has hardened herself against her young ones, as though she bereaved not herself: she labours in vain without fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:17",
      "text": "For God has withholden wisdom from her, and not given her a portion in understanding.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:18",
      "text": "In her season she will lift herself on high; she will scorn the horse and his rider.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:19",
      "text": "Hast thou invested the horse with strength, and clothed his neck with terror?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:20",
      "text": "And hast thou clad him in perfect armour, and made his breast glorious with courage?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:21",
      "text": "He paws exulting in the plain, and goes forth in strength into the plain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:22",
      "text": "He laughs to scorn a king as he meets him, and will by no means turn back from the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:23",
      "text": "The bow and sword resound against him; and his rage will swallow up the ground:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:24",
      "text": "and he will not believe until the trumpet sounds.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:25",
      "text": "And when the trumpet sounds, he says, Aha! and afar off he smells the war with prancing and neighing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:26",
      "text": "And does the hawk remain steady by thy wisdom, having spread out her wings unmoved, looking toward the region of the south?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:27",
      "text": "And does the eagle rise at thy command, and the vulture remain sitting over his nest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:28",
      "text": "on a crag of a rock, and in a secret place?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:29",
      "text": "Thence he seeks food, his eyes observe from far.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.39.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 39,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 39:30",
      "text": "And his young ones roll themselves in blood, and wherever the carcases may be, immediately they are found.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
